Basic structure of java program
1.Functions: These are the small chunks of code which perform some specific task.
that can be addition, Subtraction, multiplication etc.
Functions are also called Method in java.
Function can be static or dynamic in nature.

2. Classes: It is a blueprint in java for creating Object
Basically class defines Structure and behaviour of Object.
A class contain Variables.
A class may or may not contain function

------------------------------------------NAMING CONVENTION in JAVA-------------------------------------------------
PascalConvention: Used for Class
First letter is capital
ex, MyNameIsNikhil
AddTwoNumbers : Example <----------

camelCaseConvention: Used for Function
First letter is lower case
addTwoNumbers: Example <-----------
